-- Day 01: Introduction to SQL

-- What is Data?
-- Data can be text, numbers, images, videos, or documents.
-- Any raw fact or information is called data.

-- What is Database?
-- A database is a collection of data stored in an organized way.
-- Databases help in storing and managing large amounts of data.

-- What is SQL?
-- SQL stands for Structured Query Language.
-- SQL is used to interact with databases.
-- It is not a programming language, it is a query language.

-- Why we use SQL?
-- Simplifies working with large database
-- Enables easy and Efficient data management
-- SQL is universal & work with most database system.
-- To retrieve data
-- To update data
-- To delete data
-- Applicable on relational database(data stored in table format)

-- Where SQL is used?
-- Data Analyst
-- Data Scientist
-- Business Analyst
-- Backend Developer
-- SQL Developer

-- Purpose of storing Data in Database
-- Easily accessed
-- Modified
-- Protected
-- Analyzed

-- What are Queries?
-- Queries are commands used to retrieve, insert, update,
    or delete data stored in a database.
-- Imagine a shop register (database).
    Asking the shopkeeper to show products, add new items,
    change prices, or remove expired items is similar to writing queries.

-- Example of SQL Queries:
-- SELECT query:
SELECT * FROM students;
-- Used to fetch data from a table.
